description: Keep React component files focused on component definitions
alwaysApply: true
---

# Component File Organization

- Component files should only define and export React components.
- Define only one React component per file. Extract additional components into their own nearby component files before finishing the change.
- Keep custom hooks in their own nearby `use-*.ts` or `use-*.tsx` files.
- Keep constants in nearby `constants.ts` files.
- Keep utility functions in nearby utility files named for the helper, such as `get-status-message.ts`.
- Prefer colocating these files as close as possible to the components that use them.
- Do not add non-component helpers at the bottom of a component file; extract them before finishing the change.
